  "notes": "Standard Slovenian. Unique among Slavic languages: retains a dual number in grammar. ⟨l⟩ → [w] in syllable coda (e.g. *delal* [dɛˈlaw]). ⟨v⟩ is variable [v ~ ʋ ~ w ~ f] depending on context. Standard language has phonemic pitch accent (tone); many dialects are toneless. No palatal stops (unlike Czech/Slovak), but ⟨lj nj⟩ = [ʎ ɲ].",
